<HEADLINE> Quotes on Kevorkian's Verdict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	--''Dr. Kevorkian will be lauded in history as a hero.'' --  
Kevorkian attorney David Gorosh. 

</P>
<P>
	--''It's not going to be solved by someone holding a gun to the  
head of society and saying this is the way it's going to be 
done.''-- Prosecutor John Skrzynski, on the future of the 
assisted-suicide debate. 

</P>
<P>
	--''I think as a practical matter he'll go to prison, and  
prisoners don't have press conferences. In a way, he's kind of 
silenced himself in doing this.'' -- Skrzynski. 

</P>
<P>
	--''He definitely did not accomplish his goal. What he did was  
bring about his own self-destruction ... not the goal of continuing 
to make advancements to protect the freedom of all of us against 
government interference.'' -- Geoffrey Fieger, Kevorkian's former 
attorney. 

</P>
<P>
	-- ``We believe the verdict should have been premeditated murder,  
but we're very elated by the second-degree verdict. We want to see 
Jack Kevorkian imprisoned for life. It's clear he has no respect 
for the law, but even less respect for people with disabilities.'' 
-- Diane Coleman, president of an organization called Not Dead Yet. 
</P>
