<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stephen Got Even Wins at Turfway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FLORENCE, Ky. (AP) -- Stephen Got Even, trained by Nick Zito,  
circled the field on the far turn and pulled away in the stretch to 
win the $750,000 Gallery Furniture.com Stakes at Turfway Park 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Straight Man, trained by Bob Baffert, went off the 2-1 favorite.  
He set a slow pace and led to the top of the stretch. Then jockey 
Shane Seller made a big move on the outside with Stephen Got Even 
and pulled away through the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
	The winning time for the 1 1/8-mile race was 1:49 on a fast track --  
well off Hansel's track record of 1:46 3-5 in this race when it was 
called the Jim Beam Stakes. 
</P>
<P>
	Stephen Got Even finished 2 1/2 lengths ahead of K One King. Epic  
Honor was third, and Straight Man faded to fourth. 
</P>
<P>
	Baffert had spent most of the day in airplanes to see Straight  
Man's Triple Crown potential in person. 
</P>
<P>
	From Dubai, where Silver Charm is running in the $5 million  
Dubai World Cup Sunday, Baffert spent eight hours on a plane to 
London, caught another flight to New York, then took a private jet 
to Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky International Airport, which is 
nearly adjacent to Turfway Park. 
</P>
<P>
	He arrived on the grounds about 45 minutes before post time.  
</P>
<P>
	Stephen Got Even paid $16, $7 and $5.20. K One King returned  
$4.60 and $3.80. Epic Honor was $5 to show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
