<HEADLINE> Oliver Stone Must Give Deposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AMITE, La. (AP) -- Oliver Stone has been ordered to give a  
deposition in a lawsuit that claims his film ``Natural Born 
Killers'' was responsible for the shooting of a convenience store 
clerk. 
</P>
<P>
	The director is scheduled to give testimony on April 14 in  
Amite, La., said Joe Simpson, an attorney for the family of Patsy 
Byers, who was paralyzed in a robbery-shooting involving two 
teen-agers in 1995. She died of cancer in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	The family filed suit against Stone and Time Warner, which was  
involved in the movie's production and release. Their lawsuit says 
Sarah Edmondson shot Byers while Benjamin Darrus waited outside a 
Louisiana store, and that the two were inspired to commit the crime 
by watching the movie. 
</P>
<P>
	Stone's attorney, Alton Lewis, claimed the suit threatens First  
Amendment rights to free speech. But the U.S. Supreme Court on 
March 8 denied a review of a state appeals court ruling that the 
case should not be dismissed, and sent it back to the Louisiana 
court. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewis was out of the office Friday and could not comment, his  
office said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
