<DOCNO> APW19990327.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-27 12:11:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Son of Media Mogul Gets Married </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	YASS, Australia (AP) -- The media prince and the beauty queen  
were married Saturday in a wedding that not even pouring rain could 
spoil. 
</P>
<P>
	Lachlan Murdoch, the 27-year-old heir apparent to father  
Rupert's global media empire, exchanged vows with Australian model 
Sarah O'Hare, 26, at the family's sprawling riverside property at 
Cavan in the Australian Outback, near the national capital 
Canberra. 
</P>
<P>
	The wedding was shrouded in secrecy, although one of the  
nation's worst kept secrets. It was confirmed when official 
photographs were published on the Web site of Murdoch's News Ltd. 
</P>
<P>
	In a statement posted on the site, News Ltd. said 100 guests  
including the parents of the bride and groom attended the service, 
conducted in a marquee erected on the banks of the Muribidgee 
River. 
</P>
<P>
	A reception was held on the property, including champagne and  
fireworks at sunset. 
</P>
</TEXT>
