<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The sky was mostly clear and dry over much of the Plains this  
morning, from Minnesota through eastern Texas. Stubborn low 
pressure continued to produce some light precipitation over the 
Mid-Atlantic. 
</P>
<P>
	Much of the East was free of any cloud cover. And in the West,  
light showers fell across northern Nevada and Idaho. 
</P>
<P>
	Low pressure was forecast to work its way along the mid-Atlantic  
coast and push moisture towards lower New England. There was a 
possibility of rain across east Pennsylvania and New Jersey, into 
lower New England. 
</P>
<P>
	In the central states, thundershowers were possible in Nebraska  
-- along with blustery winds. 
</P>
<P>
	Mostly cloudy skies and scattered showers were expected in  
Montana, Idaho, Wyoming, and Colorado. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures were expected in the 40s and 50s from the Northeast  
to the northern Plains; in the 60s along much of the West Coast and 
the middle Plains; in the 70s and 80s in the Southwest; and in the 
70s in southern Florida. 
</P>
<P>
	Thursday's high temperature in the U.S. mainland was 86 degrees  
in Fort Lauderdale, Fla. The low was 10 degrees in Marquette, Mich. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
